		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr><td><P>
     My name is Justin i am a player on the Bertoxxy Server by the name of Rubin, i have a question "Why do we have to Pay?" I mean it would be a Dream of having to pay like 10$ every 2 months or say 4.95$ a month i mean im not broke or anything but paying gets to be a pain in the neck, We the people of EverQuest wish that you lower prices of monthly fee or completey Eliminate price, we work (do chores whatever) and a certain % of our money goes into the price to play a fun game with Friends Allys and Enemys, so we are honest paying customers but i would believe you would get even more people playing your Wonderful game if you Lowered Prices. If prices were eliminated then gaming would be much funner and without worrying about price to play many more would play, if you were to lower price lower to somethin reasonable say 4.95$ or somethin. Also what is used to charge in Canadian Currency? US money is worth more than Canadian Currency so do they get off the hook? <P>

         -Justin Timoney

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   EverQuest has very high upkeep costs.  That's why you continue to
pay to play.  We've got servers to maintain, we've got in-game help
staff to pay, we've got content-makers to pay (do you think that the
optional extra zones materialized from thin air?), and we've got sports
cars to buy (if we can't enjoy the fruits of our labors, then we ain't
doin' the labors), among other things.  There, question answered.<P>

<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

     Ok I have been playing EQ for about a year now and I love the game, but I have noticed something that i find very mundain and that is the attacking of the characters,   have you every seen a karate chop Batman .. add a sword and **POFF**  you have an EQ character (exculding the Monk class).<P>

  So my question is is there any plans to introduce new weapon attacks for the characters,  there is nothing I would rather do than as a vile creature is running from me than to hit a hot key and trust my sword into the creatures back or slash at him or any thing besides CHOP CHOP CHOP CHOP  "yawn" .  Just an idea or thought I had while watching my character CHOP at his target... ( excluding some small special attacks from the rouge "backstab" monk "kick" "tiger punch" ect.. )   I hope you can understand what I am asking, it does not have to be more damage just differnt motion of the characters.  Thanks for you time  :)

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   I sympathize with you, but I'm not aware that there are any plans to
make character animation more diverse.  I don't think that we have the
manpower for that, any more than we have the manpower to create
more character models of unique build than I am able to construct.
Rick Schmitz is our only animator, and unfortunately, his plate is full of
more crucial work.<P>

<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 Hello Milo!<P>
 
 I would like to compliment you on the work that you did in EverQuest.  I dont know all of the graphical stuff you did, but since all of it is top notch(except the oil cans that humans use as helmets).  I realy like the new iksar character work, especialy the platemail helmet(which is better than the oil cans =p)<P>

  Well, im just going to compliment you on anything and everything you have done, since its all good.  Thanks for what the stuff you had a part in creating for EverQuest.  Oh well, im sure you have heard all of this before, but I couldn't resist telling you myself.<P>
 
 -Will M.

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

